      "span_text": "The murine microglial cell line, BV-2, was cultured in Dulbecco's modified essential medium (DMEM; Applied Scientific, San Francisco, CA) containing 5% heat-inactivated fetal calf serum (Hyclone, Ogden, UT), 4 mM L-glutamine, 0.2 mM penicillin, 0.05 mM streptomycin, and 20 mM HEPES (Sigma, St. Louis, MO) at 37uC in a CO 2 incubator [CITATION_1] ."
